<br>
What if their goal was to kill all 4 warders and wake the sleeper, seeing that game lore proves that waking him is basically the equivalent of finishing the game.<br>
<br>
What if they were all about to quit and just decided they wanted to &quot;finish the game&quot; and that was their goal.<br>
<br>
It's not selfish to think that way, it's jsut being open-minded enuff to realize that when it comes to things like this, you sometimes have to just say fuck everyone else and do what you wanna do.  I don't think it's anyone's goal to play this game and be liked.<br>
<br>
Given Enchanters/Necromancers/Magicians can actually charm 600DPS pets and camp mini-bosses in the planes, I don't see anyone /rant'ing on this board about that, and that's the reason why they nerfed those spells.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can't get my spell because overpowered Enc.'s are camping all the turnins and selling them for high prices&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's unfair because they can get an AA point every 20 minutes&quot;<br>
<br>
You wanna know what kind of stuff is really worth ranting about?<br>
<br>
Think about how you would feel if your guild leader Ebay'ed and sold the guild's bank account with his character.  How would you feel then?  You actually invested the time to get all those uber drops from VT and he sells it all for a mere $200.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, even though I may be blunt and stuck to reality, I can somewhat feel your *pain*, but you have to realize that you aren't the only ones in the game with *goals*, no matter how many you have behind you, whether it's one person or 99.999999999999999999999999999999% of the server.  And some people's goals may very well end your very chance at achieving yours.  I've been playing this game for a very long time (have numerous deleted 50+ char; 50 was max level in the *early* days of the game) and for many, dying to this unkillable mob is the epitome of the game.<br>
<br>
That action itself is a goal obtained and the only reason why guilds refuse to do it is because they have pity for the up and coming.  News flash, You really don't mean anything to anyone in this game.  You are just another way for them to achieve their goals, and it's the same for everyone, even me.<br>
<br>
Sad, yes, but true.  The only way to go about dealing with these things is to say &quot;so fucking what&quot; and deal with it.  Yes, you can blacklist them.  You can ban them.  You can deny them service and harrass them with every word that you can come up in your petty little head (refer to www.dictionary.com plz <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), but it won't change anything.<br>
<br>
Sleeper is not sleeping anymore, and he won't go back to sleep anymore, so wasting your time bitching about it won't change anything.  Any by outcasting them, you've pretty much fucked yourself because now they will make it a mission to do everything they can to provoke a /rant out of you =/<br>
<br>
You're playing right into their game, and they like it!<br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
<br>
Congratz, you have been <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :owned --><img src=http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/smilies/owned.gif ALT=":owned"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  by Hawkestone!<br>
